• Developer Portal

Theatres

V2

The Theatres endpoint provides information on multiple AMC Theatres.

Endpoints

Verb Endpoint Description
GET /v2/theatres Get all Active Theatres
GET /v2/theatres/{id} Get a Theatre by Theatre Id.
GET /v2/theatres/{slug} Get a Theatre by slug.
GET /v2/theatres/views/now-playing/wwm-release-number/{wwm-release-number} Get theatres now playing the specified WWM release number.

Theatres Query Parameters

  • You may optionally supply a include-attributes query string parameter to specify a comma delimited list of attributes that the theatres must have.
    • If one isn't provided all theatres will be returned.
    • Visit here to browse the full list of options
  • You may optionally supply a exclude-attributes query string parameter to specify a comma delimited list of attributes that the theatres must not have.
    • If one isn't provided all theatres will be returned.
    • Visit here to browse the full list of options
  • You may optionally supply a attribute-operator query string parameter to specify if your included or excluded attributes should be inclusive or exclusive.
    • If one isn't provided all showtimes will be returned.
    • Options Include:
      • and
      • or
  • You may optionally supply a ids query string parameter to retrieve multiple theatre records matching the specified comma-delimited theatre ids.
  • You may optionally supply a name query string parameter to search for a theatre whose name contains the specified text.
  • You may optionally supply a market query string parameter to search for a theatre in the specified market.
  • You may optionally supply a state query string parameter to search for a theatre in the specified state (Required if city parameter provided).
  • You may optionally supply a city query string parameter to search for a theatre in the specified city (Requires state parameter).
  • You may optionally supply a brand query string parameter to search for a theatre with a specific brand.
  • You may optionally supply a include query string parameter to search closed theatres.
    • Options Include:
      • closed
  • You may optionally supply a page-number query string parameter to specify which page of results to retrieve.
    • If one isn't provided the results will begin with the first page (a value of 1 will be used).
  • You may optionally supply a page-size query string parameter to specify the number of results per page.
    • If one isn't provided a default of 10 will be used.

Theatres Properties

Name Description
pageSize The number of results included for each page, up to a maximum of 100. Defaults to 10.
pageNumber The page number returned.
count The total number of results available across all pages.
_embedded.Theatres A list of Theatre Representations returned.

Theatres Links

Relation Description Verbs Templated
self The current list of theatres results. GET No
previous The previous page of theatres results. GET No
next The next page of theatres results. GET No

Theatre


Theatre Properties

Name Description
id The theatre id.
name The name of the theatre.
longName The long name of the theatre.
secondaryLongName The secondary long name of the theatre.
showtimesPhoneNumber The phone number to call to inquire about showtimes.
guestServicesPhoneNumber The guest services phone number.
utcOffset The current UTC Offset of the theatre's timezone.
timezone The timezone where the theatre is located.
timezoneAbbreviation The timezone abbreviation where the theatre is located.
slug The theatre slug.
facebookUrl The url for the theatre's fan page on facebook
outageDescription The reason the theatre is temporarily closed if applicable
websiteUrl The website url for the theatre on amctheatres.com
directionsUrl The Url for an image of a map to used for directions to the theatre.
loyaltyVersion The version of AMC's loyalty program offered by the theatre.
isClosed An indicator that the theatre is closed.
closures A list of theatre closures.
lastBusinessDate The date that the theatre closed.
attributes A list of theatre attributes.
location.addressLine1 The theatre's address line 1.
location.addressLine2 The theatre's address line 2.
location.city The theatre's city.
location.postalCode The theatre's postal code in 5 or 9 digit format
location.state The theatre's state abbreviation.
location.stateName The theatre's full state name.
location.country The theatre's country.
location.latitude The theatre's latitude in decimal format.
location.longitude The theatre's longitude in decimal format.
location.marketName The theatre's market name.
location.marketId The theatre's market id.
media.theatreImageIcon The theatre's image icon.
media.theatreImageStandard The theatre's large image.
media.theatreImageThumbnail The theatre's thumbnail image.
media.theatreImageLarge The theatre's image icon.
media.heroDesktopDynamic The theatre's Hero Desktop Dynamic image.
media.heroMobileDynamic The theatre's Hero Mobile Dynamic image.
media.interiorDynamic The theatre's Interior Dynamic image.
media.exteriorDynamic The theatre's Exterior Dynamic image.
media.promotionDynamic The theatre's Promotion Dynamic image.
redemptionMethods A list of redemption methods supported by the theatre.
westWorldMediaTheatreNumber The West World Media theatre number.
concessionsDeliveryOptions A list of Concession Delivery Options eg. DeliveryToSeat, ExpressPickup.
convenienceFeeTaxPercent Tax rate percentage at which convenience fee tax is calculated. Use this only if flat tax amount is zero.
convenienceFeeTaxFlatAmount Flat tax amount for convenience fee.
brand The theatre's brand abbreviation.
  • AMC
  • DIT
  • Classic
productSubscriptionUsageLevel An indicator that signifies the theatre's tier level.
onlineConcessions Indicates whether the theatre supports ordering online concessions.
hasMultipleKitchens Indicates whether the theatre has multiple kitchens used for express pickup concession orders.
estimatedConcessionsOrderFees Estimated concession order fees for the theatre. Express Pick Up and/or Delivery to Seat fees.


Theatre Links

Relation Description Methods Templated
self The current theatre representation. GET No
https://api.amctheatres.com/rels/v2/theatre-seating-layouts Returns a list of seating layouts for the Theatre. GET No

Attribute


Attribute Properties

Name Description
name The display name
description The attribute description.
code The unique identifier for queries.

Closure


Closure Properties

Name Description
startDateTimeUtc The closure start date/time (UTC).
endDateTimeUtc The closure end date/time (UTC), null if indefinite.


Examples

Get all theatres
GET  /v2/theatres

GET  /v2/theatres?state=alabama

  "pageSize": 10,
